<paragraph id="755D36A03125FFC2FF4DFC220C04FC45" blockId="3.[182,607,958,980]" box="[182,607,958,980]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<heading id="2E1581CC3125FFC2FF4DFC220C04FC45" box="[182,607,958,980]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FF4DFC220C04FC45" authority="(Mannerheim)" baseAuthorityName="Mannerheim" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[182,607,958,980]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microrhopala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrolineata">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FF4DFC220C04FC45" bold="true" box="[182,607,958,980]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FF4DFC220F9BFC45" bold="true" box="[182,448,958,980]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Microrhopala rubrolineata</emphasis>
(Mannerheim)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="755D36A03125FFC2FF54FC760F7DF9BC" blockId="3.[151,638,1002,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
On 
<date id="015C10603125FFC2FF22FC760FC4FC6E" box="[217,415,1002,1023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" value="2012-11-08">8 November 2012</date>
, in Madera Canyon, 
<collectingRegion id="B726F8423125FFC2FF6CFB980EBDFB88" box="[151,230,1028,1049]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, I found a single leaf mine on 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FDDBFB980F3AFBA5" authority="A. Gray" authorityName="A. Gray" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Brickellia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betonicifolia">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FDDBFB980F55FBA5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Brickellia betonicifolia</emphasis>
A. Gray
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FE95FB830F80FBA5" box="[366,475,1055,1076]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
). It was transparent and followed the leaf edge, with abundant frass in the form of long, narrow threads or strips (
<figureCitation id="EDD92A253125FFC2FDC2FBC80C29FBF8" box="[569,626,1108,1129]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[196,236,1172,1191]" captionTargetBox="[172,1192,183,1148]" captionTargetId="figure-206@4.[172,1193,183,1149]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 7â€“12. 7) Presumed mine of Microrhopala rubrolineata in Brickellia betonicifolia leaf; 8) Brickellia betonicifolia leaf with skeletonizing by adult Octotoma marginicollis. The mine along the leaf margin was possibly made by a larva of this species; 9) Hog-peanut (Amphicarpaea bracteata) leaf with mine of Odontota mundula overlapping mine of Leucanthiza amphicarpeaefoliella. The latter is visible as an indistinct band of frass in the lower left; 10) Mine of Odontota scapularis in groundnut leaf, with excrement-covered egg mass at right edge of photo; 11) Odontota scapularis egg mass containing pupae of parasitoid wasps; 12) Mine of Stenopodius texanus in Abutilon leaf." pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Since the mine had a parasitoid exit hole, I opened it and photographed the larval remains, which were definitely coleopteran. Just two hispines have been associated with 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FED6FB220FEAFB42" authority="Ell." authorityName="Ell." box="[301,433,1214,1235]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Brickellia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FED6FB220FD3FB42" box="[301,392,1214,1235]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Brickellia</emphasis>
Ell.
</taxonomicName>
, in both cases only as adults, and both species have been found in Madera Canyon (
<bibRefCitation id="11734B513125FFC2FF17FB6F0F3DFA99" author="Staines &amp; Catalog of the hispines of the world. Available from &amp; / Collections &amp; Accessed May" box="[236,358,1267,1288]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" refId="ref7401" refString="Staines, C. L. 2012. Catalog of the hispines of the world. Available from: entomology. si. edu / Collections _ Coleoptera-Hispines. html (Accessed May 2014)." type="book" year="2012">Staines 2012</bibRefCitation>
; C. L. Staines 
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FE12FB680C7BFA98" box="[489,544,1268,1289]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">in litt.</emphasis>
). The two remaining front legs of this larva were segmented, ruling out 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FF02FAB50C49FAAC" authority="Horn." authorityName="Horn." box="[249,530,1320,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Octotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginicollis">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FF02FAB50F8EFAAF" box="[249,469,1321,1342]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Octotoma marginicollis</emphasis>
Horn.
</taxonomicName>
The immature stages of the other species, 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FE39FADF0C0DFAC9" baseAuthorityName="Mannerheim" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[450,598,1347,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microrhopala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrolineata">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FE39FADF0C0DFAC9" box="[450,598,1347,1368]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">M. rubrolineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are unknown, but C. L. Staines (
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FE33FAC20C52FAE2" box="[456,521,1374,1395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">in litt.</emphasis>
) suggested that the larva I photographed was consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FF6CFA0F0FC1FA39" authority="Chevrolat. If" authorityName="Chevrolat. If" box="[151,410,1427,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microrhopala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FF6CFA0F0F42FA39" box="[151,281,1427,1448]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Microrhopala</emphasis>
Chevrolat. If
</taxonomicName>
future rearing can confirm this as a larval host, it will be the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FF4EFA540F66FA4C" box="[181,317,1480,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microrhopala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4796EAB23125FFC2FF4EFA540F66FA4C" box="[181,317,1480,1501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Microrhopala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae feeding on a host in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FF31FA7E0F66FA66" box="[202,317,1506,1527]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Eupatorieae">Eupatorieae</taxonomicName>
. All known larval hosts of North American species are in 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FE73FA610F81F983" box="[392,474,1533,1554]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Astereae">Astereae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B2E24D233125FFC2FDF6FA610F79F9BC" authority="(Staines 2012)" baseAuthorityName="Staines" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Heliantheae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
Heliantheae (
<bibRefCitation id="11734B513125FFC2FF65F9840F47F9BC" author="Staines &amp; Catalog of the hispines of the world. Available from &amp; / Collections &amp; Accessed May" box="[158,284,1560,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" refId="ref7401" refString="Staines, C. L. 2012. Catalog of the hispines of the world. Available from: entomology. si. edu / Collections _ Coleoptera-Hispines. html (Accessed May 2014)." type="book" year="2012">Staines 2012</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
